main event: Two cones of orange light were observed by five people near O'Hare International Airport in Chicago, Illinois on July 11, 1962.
interesting points: The objects were described as two cones of light, 3-12 feet in size, and orange in color.
The objects traveled a distance of 15-20 feet from Kankakee to Chicago and then disappeared over the horizon.
The objects moved in a straight path for about 15 minutes.
The sighting was made by five people using binoculars.
The sighting occurred at 0220 DLS (Daylight Saving Time).
location: Near O'Hare International Airport, Chicago, Illinois
